        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "B2 Let S be the set of all ordered triples (p, q, r) of prime numbers for which at least one rational number x satis- fies px2 + qx + r = 0. which primes appear in seven or more elements of S?",
        "bbox": [
          0.5325490196078432,
