        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "A2 Let a1, a2, .. and b1, b2, . .. be sequences of positive real numbers such that a1 = b1 = 1 and bn = bn−1an − 2 for n = 2, 3, . .. Assume that the sequence (bj) is bounded. Prove that",
        "bbox": [
          0.1011764705882353,
          0.3296969696969697,
          0.49098039215686273,
          0.3878787878787879
        ],
        "order": 8
