        "id": "mineru_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2011_Problems_2011_page_001_15",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "B3 Let f and g be (real-valued) functions defined on an open interval containing O, with g nonzero and contin- uous at 0. If fg and f /g are differentiable at 0, must f be differentiable at 0?",
